<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q2 — Transcendental number</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[Which of the following is transcendental over \(\mathbb{Q}\)?]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(\pi\).</strong><br>By Lindemann's theorem (1882), \(\pi\) is transcendental over \(\mathbb{Q}\). The other choices are algebraic: \(\sqrt{2}\) satisfies \(x^2-2=0\); \(\sqrt[3]{3}\) satisfies \(x^3-3=0\); \(i=\sqrt{-1}\) satisfies \(x^2+1=0\). Also, \(e\) is transcendental (Hermite, 1873).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
