<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q3 — Minimal polynomial of √2</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The minimal polynomial of \(\sqrt{2}\) over \(\mathbb{Q}\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(x^2-2\).</strong><br>\(x^2-2\) is monic, has \(\sqrt{2}\) as a root, and is irreducible over \(\mathbb{Q}\) (by Eisenstein with \(p=2\)). The minimal polynomial is the unique monic irreducible polynomial in \(\mathbb{Q}[x]\) having \(\sqrt{2}\) as a root. It has degree 2, so \([\mathbb{Q}(\sqrt{2}):\mathbb{Q}]=2\).</p>]]></text>
