<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q5 — Tower law</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[If \(F\subseteq K\subseteq L\) are fields with \([L:F]=10\) and \([K:F]=5\), then \([L:K]\) equals:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: 2.</strong><br>The Tower Law states \([L:F]=[L:K]\cdot[K:F]\). So \([L:K]=\frac{[L:F]}{[K:F]}=\frac{10}{5}=2\).</p>]]></text>
