<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q6 — Simple extension isomorphism</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[If \(\alpha\) is algebraic over \(F\) with minimal polynomial \(f(x)\in F[x]\), then \(F(\alpha)\) is isomorphic to:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(F[x]/(f(x))\).</strong><br>The evaluation map \(\phi:F[x]\to F(\alpha)\) sending \(x\mapsto\alpha\) is surjective with kernel \((f(x))\) (since \(f\) is the minimal polynomial, i.e., the generator of \(\ker\phi\)). By the First Isomorphism Theorem, \(F(\alpha)\cong F[x]/(f(x))\).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
