<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q7 — Finite field Fpn</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The number of elements in the finite field \(\mathbb{F}_{p^n}\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(p^n\).</strong><br>\(\mathbb{F}_{p^n}\) is the unique (up to isomorphism) field with \(p^n\) elements, where \(p\) is prime and \(n\ge 1\). It is the splitting field of \(x^{p^n}-x\) over \(\mathbb{F}_p\). The extension \(\mathbb{F}_{p^n}/\mathbb{F}_p\) has degree \(n\) and is Galois with cyclic Galois group generated by Frobenius.</p>]]></text>
