<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q8 — Degree [Q(ζₙ):Q]</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[If \(\zeta_n\) is a primitive \(n\)-th root of unity, then \([\mathbb{Q}(\zeta_n):\mathbb{Q}]\) equals:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(\varphi(n)\).</strong><br>The minimal polynomial of \(\zeta_n\) over \(\mathbb{Q}\) is the cyclotomic polynomial \(\Phi_n(x)\), which has degree \(\varphi(n)\) (Euler's totient). This polynomial is irreducible over \(\mathbb{Q}\). The extension \(\mathbb{Q}(\zeta_n)/\mathbb{Q}\) is Galois with group \(\mathrm{Gal}(\mathbb{Q}(\zeta_n)/\mathbb{Q})\cong(\mathbb{Z}/n\mathbb{Z})^\times\).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
