<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q9 — Normal extension</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[A field extension \(K/F\) is called normal if:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Every irreducible polynomial in \(F[x]\) that has one root in \(K\) splits completely in \(K\).</strong><br>Equivalently, \(K\) is the splitting field of a family of polynomials over \(F\). A finite extension is normal iff it is a splitting field of some polynomial over \(F\). Normal + separable = Galois.</p>]]></text>
