<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q12 — Algebraic closure uniqueness</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The algebraic closure \(\overline{F}\) of a field \(F\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Unique up to \(F\)-isomorphism.</strong><br>\(\overline{F}\) is an algebraic extension of \(F\) in which every non-constant polynomial in \(F[x]\) has a root (equivalently, every polynomial in \(\overline{F}[x]\) splits completely). It exists by Zorn's Lemma and is unique up to isomorphism over \(F\). Example: \(\overline{\mathbb{Q}}\) = algebraic numbers, \(\overline{\mathbb{R}}=\mathbb{C}\).</p>]]></text>
