<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q13 — Degree 2 extension is normal</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[Every field extension of degree 2 over \(F\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Normal.</strong><br>If \([K:F]=2\), take any \(\alpha\in K\setminus F\). Its minimal polynomial \(f\) over \(F\) has degree 2 and \(\alpha\) as a root. Since \([K:F]=2=\deg f\), we have \(K=F(\alpha)\) and \(K\) is the splitting field of \(f\) over \(F\) (the other root is \(-\alpha-(\text{trace of }\alpha)\in K\)). Hence \(K/F\) is normal.</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
