<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q16 — Frobenius endomorphism</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[In a field of characteristic \(p>0\), the Frobenius map \(\phi:x\mapsto x^p\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: A field homomorphism (ring endomorphism).</strong><br>\(\phi(x+y)=(x+y)^p=x^p+y^p=\phi(x)+\phi(y)\) (using the fact that \(\binom{p}{k}\equiv 0\pmod{p}\) for \(0<k<p\)), and \(\phi(xy)=\phi(x)\phi(y)\). Since \(\phi(1)=1\), \(\phi\) is a ring homomorphism, hence an injective field map. Over a finite field it is an automorphism generating the Galois group.</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
