<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q17 — Algebraic over algebraic</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[If \(K/F\) and \(L/K\) are both algebraic extensions, then \(L/F\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Algebraic.</strong><br>Take any \(\alpha\in L\). Since \(L/K\) is algebraic, \(\alpha\) satisfies some \(f(x)=x^n+k_{n-1}x^{n-1}+\cdots+k_0\in K[x]\). Since \(K/F\) is algebraic, each \(k_i\) is algebraic over \(F\). The extension \(F(k_0,\ldots,k_{n-1},\alpha)\) is a finite extension of \(F\), hence algebraic. So \(\alpha\) is algebraic over \(F\).</p>]]></text>
