<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit IV Q22 — Minimal polynomial is irreducible</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The minimal polynomial of an algebraic element \(\alpha\) over \(F\) is always:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Monic and irreducible over \(F\).</strong><br>The minimal polynomial \(m_{\alpha,F}(x)\) is the unique monic polynomial of least degree in \(F[x]\) satisfied by \(\alpha\). It is irreducible: if \(m_{\alpha,F}=fg\) with \(\deg f,\deg g<\deg m_{\alpha,F}\), then \(f(\alpha)=0\) or \(g(\alpha)=0\), contradicting minimality. Also, \(m_{\alpha,F}\mid h\) for any \(h\in F[x]\) with \(h(\alpha)=0\).</p>]]></text>
